cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.DC 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes a joint cache-channel coding scheme and derives a multicast backhaul rate expression, which involves information theoretic concepts such as channel capacity. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with the optimization of backhaul links connecting the centralized processor with the base-stations in a cloud radio access network. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper formulates a two-timescale joint cache size allocation and beamforming design problem, which involves system optimization and control. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper considers the case with multiple files having different popularities and proposes an optimized cache size allocation scheme, which is relevant to multimedia content delivery. 
5. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper proposes the use of wireless multicast and BS caching to augment the backhaul of C-RAN, which involves distributed computing and communication.
